	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540549_01.jpg"/>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-687" type="subject">Testimony</term> taken by <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_mamet_efraim_fishl">Efraim Fishl Mamet</persName></p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_amarnikh_rokhl">Amarnikh, Rokhl</persName>, born <date when="1926-12-07">December 7, 1926</date> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/764862/miedzyrzec-podlaski.html">Międzyrzec</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>, relates: On <date when="1943-05-25">May 25,
					1943</date>, we were twenty <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>,
				among them <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, and three <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> aged from four to fifteen years old,
				lying <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hidden</term> in our house in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunker</term>. The <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> discovered our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hiding place</term>, tore up the floor with iron bars,
				and managed to reach us: we tried to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1053" type="subject">buy our
					lives</term> with money. We gave them gold and dollars to the value of 200,000 <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> zlotys, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">they took the money</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> and a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term> on the spot. I fled together with another
				two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">girls</term>. The remaining fifteen were taken
				and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term>. We found an open <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunker</term> and went in. From there observed the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">aktion</term>. This was the last <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">aktion</term> in our city. There were then in total
				5,000 Jews therein. We saw how at first the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> [men]
				took the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> by force and drove them to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">cemetery</term>, where they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> them. The remaining <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, remained in the Politzei Sqaure on
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Piekarsga Street</placeName>. This was a large square in the middle of
				the city surrounded with walls; the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480" type="subject">Jewish-ghetto
					police</term> was located there. In the square a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject"
					>selection</term> took place. Some <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>
				and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>, around 1,200 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">persons</term>, were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> straight away, the rest were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">taken away</term> to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">aktion</term> continued in this way for three days.
				When the situation calmed, those in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term>
				came out of their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hiding places</term>, among them
				also I and my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>, who had <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hidden</term> in a different <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunker</term>. Then, on <date when="1943-05-28">May
					28</date>, we were caught by <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> and <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518"
					type="subject">deported</term> to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp"
					>Majdanek</placeName>. We were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject"
					>transported</term> in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">closed wagons</term>, up
				to 150 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">wagon</term>. Arriving in <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>, a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selection</term> took place. Old <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> went straight to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">oven</term>, among them also my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">Children</term> also went directly with the elderly to
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term>. I was deemed to be among the
				healthy ones, who were taken for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> in
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work camp</term> was around 250 meters from the place
				of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematoria</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gas ovens</term>. The daily schedule in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> was as follows: the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll call</term> took place at 3.30 AM. Many <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> came out of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">barefoot</term> and stood in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">frost and snow</term> until 6 Am. We would drag out
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll call</term> and lay them on blankets spread out
				on the floor. More than one of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> would
				beg for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selection</term> so that he could go to the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term>, putting an end to his
				suffering.</p>
			<p><pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540549_02.jpg"/></p>
			<p>For <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">breakfast</term> they would give us to drink a
				bit of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">chamomile</term> [brew] and this was our
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">nourishment</term> until midday. Twelve noon
				there was a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">watery soup</term>. At 6 PM was the
				night time <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll call</term>, at which we would stand
				on our feet after an entire day at <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term>,
				sometimes three hours, because punishment <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll
					calls</term> often took place and these lasted much longer due the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">beating</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killing</term> of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term>, only then did we receive 80 grams of
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term>, ten grams of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">margarine</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">black coffee</term>. Our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> was hard physical <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">labor</term>, hacking stones, dragging brick boards
				and other physical <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">labor</term>. I was in <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName> for six weeks. On <date
					when="1943-07-16">July 16, 1943</date>, we healthy <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825"
					type="subject">women</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> were
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transported</term> to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1869" type="camp">Skarżysko-Kamienna</placeName> near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/760778/radom.html">Radom</placeName> in the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/769250/kielce.html">Kielce Voivodship</placeName>. There we <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> in an ammunition <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">factory</term> which was called Shmutz’s <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">factory</term>, number ALE 84. We <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> twelve hours per day from 6 AM to 6 PM.
				At 4 AM a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll call</term> took place, at night it
				would last until 8 PM. A punishment <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll call</term>
				would last until 9 or 9.30 PM. The nourishment: 80 grams of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
					type="subject">bread</term>. Midday: two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">watery
					soups</term> with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">rotting beats</term>, as well
				as 10 grams of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">marmalade</term>. We made grenades
				and 2 centimeter bullets. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">People</term> were often
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> by exploding material. Some became
				completely yellow due to the picric acid (such a material which is put into the grenades). <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">Selections</term> also took place. The weak would not
				be taken to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematoria</term>, since there were
				none, but would be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> at the firing range.
				Out of 540 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, among them 120 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, 40 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> remained alive and among the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> 60. As the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians">Russian</term> front neared, after we have been there fourteen months, in <date
					when="1944-09">September 1944</date>, we were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject"
					>evacuated</term> to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2879139/leipzig.html">Leipzig</placeName> together with the entire
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. Also to an ammunition <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">factory</term>, which was called SC ALE 1. There we
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> in somewhat better <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">living conditions</term>, however <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selections</term> took place from time to time, the
				weaker would be taken away and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term>,
				exactly to where I do not know. We were there for nine whole months. In <date when="1945-04">April 1945</date>, when the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1029" type="subject">American army</term> began to near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2879139/leipzig.html">Leipzig</placeName>, they took us out of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term> at night and, together with the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> men, we started <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">wandering</term> on foot over the fields and forests
				of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName>. There was already nowhere to
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuate</term> us to because the fire of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> had reached all corners of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName>, they dragged us around like this for
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">three weeks</term>. The 250 grams of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> for the journey, which they gave us when
				we left <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2879139/leipzig.html">Leipzig</placeName>, had already run out long ago, we would eat
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">grass</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">raw potatoes</term>. When the Nazis noticed this, they
				would <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shoot</term> at us, and more than one person
				was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term> running to grab <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potatoes</term> or grass form a field. The <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> would</p>
			<p><pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540549_03.jpg"/></p>
			<p>warn the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-637" type="subject">surrounding peasants</term> that they should
				beware of the stoylayz, meaning the thieves that they were driving onwards. They took from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2879139/leipzig.html">Leipzig</placeName> 12,000 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">persons</term>. Seeing that it was difficult to
				wander around with such a large group, they divided us into [smaller] groups and each group <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">wandered</term> in a different direction. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">camp commandant</term> would drive around from group
				to group in a taxi, holding a map in his hand, and wherever the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477"
					type="subject">Oberscharführer</term> would order, there they would take us. Usually these were places where the fire of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> was still a little way off. My group
				numbered 4,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, of which 1,200
				survived. Our group was mainly Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>
				from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czechoslovakia</placeName>. So we <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">walked on foot</term> for 600 kilometers. We went
				through all of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2842566/saxony.html">Saxony</placeName>, and together with the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS men</orgName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1078" type="subject">allied armies</term>. When the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS men</orgName> no longer had anywhere left to take us, they
				abandoned us under the open sky and the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians">Russians</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberated</term> us on <date when="1945-05-07">May
					7, 1945</date> (it was a Monday) in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2916851/grossdorf.html">Großdorf</placeName> near
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2955770/apolda.html">Apolda</placeName> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2842566/saxony.html">Saxony</placeName>.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_amarnikh_rokhl">Rokhel Amarnikh</persName></p>
